 So, here's a couple things we can do.

99
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,680
 So, there is this user object

100
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,120
 that in a sense is passed in.

101
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,400
 You don't have to do anything to pass it in.

102
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,360
 There's this user object that sits there

103
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:13,360
 in your template context that's automatically,

104
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,560
 we'll talk later about how you can sort of inject

105
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,280
 into every template certain little miniature,

106
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,200
 certain little things that you gotta inject.

107
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,560
 But, the system injects this user.

108
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,200
 There is an attribute called isAuthenticated,

109
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,800
 which is true or false,

110
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,720
 to say whether you're not logged in or are logged in.

111
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:33,560
 And so, if we see it, we say,

112
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,280
 oh, what's their person's full name?

113
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:37,880
 User.email, user.id.

114
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,440
 User.id is the primary key.

115
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:42,440
 We might actually have a, later we'll have a foreign key

116
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,000
 that goes into the user table,

117
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,680
 and we need to know what the primary key

118
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:49,240
 of the current user is so we can populate our foreign key

119
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,160
 so when we like have a row and it's owned by such and so,

120
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,880
 we're gonna actually put a foreign key into a table

121
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,880
 that we didn't even create.

122
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:59,400
 But, the thing I'm talking about now is you can get a URL,

123
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,160
 that URL tag, that's looking up the name of a view.

124
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,000
 Logout is the name of a view.

125
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,800
 Login is the name of a view.

126
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,840
 And then we have this question mark next equals.

127
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,400
 That's the parameter to say,

128
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,720
 when you're all done with that login or logout,

129
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:16,240
 go back to this particular URL, okay?

130
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,240
 And so,

131
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:21,320
 and so that says, go to the URL

132
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:25,840
 that's in the Authzy application, the view named open.

